Fulton E. BURKE, Appellant, v. Margaret Lee BURKE, Appellee. No. 9590. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 9, 1940. Latham & Watkins, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Wm. M. Rains, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeals in above cause dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
